#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn56.35"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.35:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.35:0.2"
msgid "4. Sīsapāvanavagga "
msgstr "4. In a Rosewood Forest "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn56.35:0.3"
msgid "35. Sattisatasutta "
msgstr "35. A Hundred Spears "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.441, sc1
msgctxt "sn56.35:1.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso vassasatāyuko vassasatajīvī. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, suppose there was a man with a lifespan of a hundred years. "

msgctxt "sn56.35:1.2"
msgid "Tamenaṃ evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "And someone might say to him: "

msgctxt "sn56.35:1.3"
msgid "‘ehambho purisa, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ taṃ sattisatena hanissanti, majjhanhikasamayaṃ sattisatena hanissanti, sāyanhasamayaṃ sattisatena hanissanti. "
msgstr "‘Come now, my good man, they’ll strike you with a hundred spears in the morning, at midday, and in the late afternoon. "

msgctxt "sn56.35:1.4"
msgid "So kho tvaṃ, ambho purisa, divase divase tīhi tīhi sattisatehi haññamāno vassasatāyuko vassasatajīvī vassasatassa accayena anabhisametāni cattāri ariyasaccāni abhisamessasī’ti. "
msgstr "And you’ll live for a hundred years being struck with three hundred spears every day. But when a hundred years have passed, you will comprehend the four noble truths for the first time.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn56.35:2.1"
msgid "Atthavasikena, bhikkhave, kulaputtena alaṃ upagantuṃ. "
msgstr "For an earnest and gentleman this is sufficient reason to submit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.35:2.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "sn56.35:2.3"
msgid "Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro; "
msgstr "Transmigration has no known beginning. "

#. VAR: asippahārānaṃ usuppahārānaṃ pharasuppahārānaṃ → asippahārānaṃ (sī1), asipahārānam parasupahārānaṃ (pā1), asippahārānaṃ pharasuppahārānaṃ (ka-ma)
msgctxt "sn56.35:2.4"
msgid "pubbā koṭi nappaññāyati sattippahārānaṃ asippahārānaṃ usuppahārānaṃ pharasuppahārānaṃ. "
msgstr "No first point is found of blows by spears, swords, arrows, and axes. "

msgctxt "sn56.35:2.5"
msgid "Evañcetaṃ, bhikkhave, assa. "
msgstr "Now this may be so. "

msgctxt "sn56.35:2.6"
msgid "Na kho panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, saha dukkhena, saha domanassena catunnaṃ ariyasaccānaṃ abhisamayaṃ vadāmi; "
msgstr "But the comprehension of the four noble truths doesn’t come with pain or sadness, I say. "

msgctxt "sn56.35:2.7"
msgid "api cāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sahāva sukhena, sahāva somanassena catunnaṃ ariyasaccānaṃ abhisamayaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr "Rather, the comprehension of the four noble truths comes only with pleasure and happiness, I say. "

msgctxt "sn56.35:2.8"
msgid "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn56.35:2.9"
msgid "Dukkhassa ariyasaccassa … pe … dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya ariyasaccassa. "
msgstr "The noble truths of suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn56.35:3.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti. "
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.35:3.2"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

